<section id="metaphor-insight" class="py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <!-- Lead-in — flows from Problem's chaos -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16" data-reveal>
      <p class="text-emerald text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">How SLOPE Works</p>
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-4">
        Structure. Methodology.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        SLOPE layers a framework on top of agent work so the output is useful to humans — not just "done" or "not done", but structured data you can learn from.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Layer 1: Structure -->
    <div class="mb-6" data-reveal>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6 sm:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-emerald/10 text-emerald font-heading font-bold text-sm shrink-0">1</span>
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-heading font-bold text-lg">Structure</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          SLOPE organizes agent work into sprints — focused batches with a clear scope, a beginning, and an end. Instead of an endless stream of sessions, each batch becomes a unit you can measure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Layer 2: Methodology -->
    <div data-reveal>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6 sm:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-emerald/10 text-emerald font-heading font-bold text-sm shrink-0">2</span>
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-heading font-bold text-lg">Methodology</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Each sprint follows a repeatable routine: set expectations, declare difficulty, execute, score the result, review what happened. This turns raw work into structured data — how hard it was, what went wrong, and whether patterns are emerging.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
